The paper proposes a machine model for evaluating different encoding schemes for visual-to-auditory sensory substitution devices, which can assist the blind in sensing the visual environment. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.SI (Sound and Music Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
